Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Protiva Biotherapeutics, Inc., a development stage biotechnology company, develops nucleic acid based pharmaceutical products. The company focuses on developing products to fight various human diseases, such as cancer, influenza, Ebola, inflammatory diseases, and chronic viral infections. Its products include Pro 1, a tumor cell growth inhibitor, which kills tumor cells and inhibits tumor growth; Pro-101, an siRNA product that acts to inhibit the production of a protein involved in tumor growth; Pro-B, which acts to inhibit the expression of a protein, apolipoprotein B; Pro-EBOV and Pro-MARV that act to inhibit the replication of the Ebola and Marburg viruses; and Stable Nucleic-Acid Lipid Particle technology, an encapsulation and delivery system for nucleic acid payloads, such as short interfering RNA (siRNA), to target cells. The company also develops Hepatitis siRNA products for the treatment of hepatitis B and C. Protiva Biotherapeutics, Inc. has a research and development facility in Vancouver, Canada. The company was founded in 2000 and is based in Seattle, Washington. As of May 30, 2008, Protiva Biotherapeutics, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Tekmira Pharmaceuticals Corp.

Description: Atargis is the first, and only, company to be able to produce sustainable, cost-effective, utility-scale, electricity from ocean waves.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: The Atargis CycCloidal Wave Energy Converter (CycWEC) is the first, and only, sustainable electricity generator that will produce cost-effective, utility-scale, electricity from ocean waves. Always on.  No batteries.  No backup.   At a technology performance level of 6.8, the 2.5 MW Atargis Cycloidal Wave Energy Converter (CycWEC) will capture 95% of the avaiable energy from each wave, then directly and efficiently convert that captured energy into electricity with technology well proven in today's wind turbine generators.  The 2.5 MW CycWEC Levelized Cost of Energy is  $0.13 per kWh.    Building on many of the principles and technologies of the wind turbine industry, like the wind turbine industry from the 1980's through 2000, the CycWEC will see a 2 to 3 times further reduction in LCOE when deployed in volume. The CycWEC utilizes a patented wave terminator generator design combined with the proprietary real-time control and optimization of underwater hydrofoils to archive this high wave-to-wire energy conversion.  It is the only ocean wave energy converter that cost effectively scales in size and power output.
